<a name="pav"></a> 
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
  <div><center><strong><h4> Recipe </h4></strong></center>
    <div class="thumbnail">
    <iframe width="350" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/YI5pCJ0__N8" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
      <h3><strong>2. Pav Bahji</strong></h3>
      <div class="caption">
        <ul>
        <li>Boil the cauliflower, peas and carrots till they are soft. Drain out the excess water.</li>
        <li>Heat the butter in a large pan, add the onion and capsicum and sauté for 2 minutes. Then, add the prepared chilli-garlic paste and sauté till the onion softens.</li>
        <li>Add the tomatoes and simmer till the oil separates. Add the turmeric powder, chilli powder, pav bhaji masala, black salt and salt and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. </li>
        <li>Add the boiled vegetables and potatoes and mash thoroughly using a potato masher, adding ½ cup of water if required.</li>
        </ul>
       </div>	
        </div>
    	</div>
    	</div>
